The paper deals with community detection in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI), systems and control (cs.SY), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of Nash dynamics in the proposed algorithms suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of game theory and decision science (cs.GT). Finally, the evaluation of the algorithms on standard benchmarks and real-world datasets suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
